A vintage 1960s-style illustration of a cluttered developer's workbench viewed from above, featuring scattered mechanical gears, vacuum tubes, and early computer punch cards intermingling with steaming coffee cups and handwritten notes on yellowed paper. In the center, a magnifying glass hovers over a tangled web of colorful wires and circuit boards, suggesting the act of debugging. The color palette uses muted browns, creams, and occasional pops of orange and teal. The scene has a worn, textured quality like an old technical manual illustration, with subtle halftone dot patterns throughout.
